name: OCCURRED
description: The word occurred is the past tense of the verb occur, which means to take place or happen. We can create a moment of movement when combining the words OCCUR and RED together. Emerging from the red nebulous ether to the right is the word RED itself. Approaching the depths of darkness is OCCUR. When these words meet an event as OCCURRED. It's an autological word zipper that bends the mind and seemingly is invisible to the eye. If no one sees it, did the actual event occur?
